  "prompt": "Which are the \"must read\" books one must go through before getting married?",
  "response": "Getting married is a significant milestone, and reading insightful books can be helpful in preparing for this important life event. Here are some \"must-read\" books that are highly recommended:\n\n1. **\"The 5 Love Languages: The Secret to Love That Lasts\" by Gary Chapman**\n   - This book explores the different ways people express and receive love, which can be invaluable for understanding your partner and fostering a strong relationship.\n\n2. **\"Things I Wish I'd Known Before We Got Married\" by Gary Chapman**\n   - Offering practical advice, this book covers essential topics that couples should discuss and understand before tying the knot.\n\n3. **\"Getting the Love You Want: A Guide for Couples\" by Harville Hendrix**\n   - This book provides insights into understanding unconscious factors that influence romantic relationships and offers exercises to enhance mutual understanding and compassion.\n\n4. **\"Hold Me Tight: Seven Conversations for a Lifetime of Love\" by Dr. Sue Johnson**\n   - Focused on Emotionally Focused Therapy (EFT), this book helps couples build lasting relationships through understanding emotional bonds.\n\n5. **\"Attached: The New Science of Adult Attachment and How It Can Help You Find - and Keep - Love\" by Amir Levine and Rachel Heller**\n   - Understanding attachment styles can be crucial for recognizing each other's needs and behaviors in a relationship.\n\n6. **\"The Seven Principles for Making Marriage Work\" by John Gottman**\n   - Based on extensive research, this book offers practical advice and exercises to strengthen relationships and resolve conflicts.\n\n7. **\"Sacred Marriage: What If God Designed Marriage to Make Us Holy More Than to Make Us Happy?\" by Gary Thomas**\n   - This book explores the spiritual aspects of marriage and suggests that personal and spiritual growth can come from the challenges and joys of married life.\n\n8. **\"Mating in Captivity: Unlocking Erotic Intelligence\" by Esther Perel**\n   - Perel dives into the dynamics of desire within long-term relationships, offering insights on maintaining intimacy and passion.\n\n9. **\"His Needs, Her Needs: Building an Affair-Proof Marriage\" by Willard F. Harley Jr.**\n   - The book discusses the different needs of partners in a marriage and how understanding and meeting these needs can prevent infidelity and strengthen the relationship.\n\n10. **\"Boundaries in Marriage\" by Dr. Henry Cloud and Dr. John Townsend**\n    - This book teaches how to set healthy boundaries within your marriage to ensure mutual respect and understanding.\n\nReading these books can provide valuable insights and practical advice to help couples navigate the complexities of married life and build a strong, healthy, and fulfilling relationship.",
